original: Högdahl, Karin Annie (Nanni), läroverksadjunkt, Motala, f. 5/10/97 i Dals-Ed, Älvsb. k, av kamr. Fingal Berg o. Ellen Bratt. G. 33 m. folk-sk /lär. David Högdahl. — Stud :ex. i Sthilm 15, fil. mag.- 20, fil. lic. 28, provar v. Upps. h. a. 1. 29-30. Res. t. Danm. 21„ Tyskl. 23, Österr. 24, Engl. 3’2, Danm. 33, Norge 34, Damm., Tyskik, Schweiz o. Itak 35. Tjg. i Vaxholm 25, Karlskrona elem :lärov. f. fl. 26, Motala 26-29, Falun 30-31, e. o. lektor i Motala 31-39, adj. i modersm. o. eng. v. Motala h. a. 1. sed. 39. Bibi. där sed. 32.
translated: Högdahl, Karin Annie (Nanni), high school teacher, Motala, born on October 5, 1897 in Dals-Ed, Älvsborg county, daughter of the businessman Fingal Berg and Ellen Bratt. Married in 1933 to the elementary school teacher David Högdahl. She passed her university exams in Stockholm in 1915, received her Master's degree in 1920, her PhD in 1928, and undertook academic positions at Uppsala University from 1929-1930. She traveled to Denmark in 1921, Germany in 1923, Austria in 1924, England in 1932, Denmark in 1933, Norway in 1934, and to Denmark, Germany, Switzerland, and Italy in 1935. She worked at Vaxholm in 1925, the Karlskrona elementary school in 1926, Motala from 1926-1929, Falun from 1930-1931, as a temporary lecturer in Motala from 1931-1939, and as a high school teacher in her mother tongue and English at Motala since 1939. She published a bibliography since 1932.
